============Neovim Movement===================

Neovim: hjkl, wbe, gg/G, i/a/o, dd, yy, p, u, /, ciw, :wq

Character Movement
h

← left

j

↓ down

k

↑ up

l

→ right

Word Movement
w

→ next word start

b

→ previous word start

e

→ word end

Line Movement
0

→ start of line

^

→ first non-space

$

→ end of line

File Movement
gg

→ top of file

G

→ bottom of file

50G

→ line 50

Insert Mode
i

→ insert before cursor

a

→ insert after cursor

I

→ insert start of line

A

→ insert end of line

o

→ new line below

O

→ new line above

Esc

→ return normal mode

Editing
x

→ delete character

dd

→ delete line

D

→ delete to line end

yy

→ copy line

p

→ paste below

P

→ paste above

u

→ undo

Ctrl-r

→ redo

Search
/text

→ search forward

?text

→ search backward

n

→ next match

N

→ previous match

Replace
:%s/old/new/g

→ replace all.

:s/old/new/g

→ replace in current line.

Visual Mode
v

→ select characters

V

→ select lines

Ctrl-v

→ block selection

Windows
:split

→ horizontal split

:vsplit

→ vertical split

Ctrl-w h

→ left window

Ctrl-w j

→ down window

Ctrl-w k

→ up window

Ctrl-w l

→ right window

Buffers
:ls

→ list buffers

:bn

→ next buffer

:bp

→ previous buffer

:bd

→ close buffer

Files
:w

→ save

:q

→ quit

:wq

→ save and quit

:q!

→ quit without saving

Advanced Vim Motions
ciw

→ change current word

diw

→ delete current word

yiw

→ copy current word

ci"

→ replace inside quotes

ci(

→ replace inside ()

ci{

→ replace inside {}

dap

→ delete paragraph

vip

→ select paragraph
